  "prompt": "My grandma has stage IV cancer with only months to live. How can I help her? She can't walk and doesn't want to do anything. I want to make her smile.",
  "response": "I'm so sorry to hear about your grandmother's condition. Here are some ways you might help and bring her comfort:\n\n1. Emotional support\n- Spend time with her\n- Listen to her stories\n- Hold her hand\n- Tell her you love her\n- Be patient and gentle\n\n2. Comfort activities\n- Read to her\n- Look through old photo albums together\n- Play soft music she enjoys\n- Watch her favorite movies/shows\n- Bring her favorite snacks if she can eat\n\n3. Practical help\n- Help with personal care\n- Assist with medications\n- Make sure she's comfortable\n- Talk to her doctors/caregivers\n\n4. Meaningful gestures\n- Create a memory book\n- Record her stories\n- Share family memories\n- Bring her small gifts\n- Write her heartfelt letters\n\n5. Entertainment\n- Bring her grandchildren/family photos\n- Show her funny videos\n- Play gentle games\n- Do simple crafts together\n\nMost importantly, just be present and show her love. Your time and affection mean more than anything else right now. Consider seeking support for yourself too, as this is emotionally challenging.\n\nWould you like to discuss any of these suggestions further?",
